# Universal Standards

## Naming

| Context | Format | Examples |
|---|---|---|
| Variables / functions | `camelCase` | `userID`, `solvedAt`, `computeScore` |
| Go exported names | `PascalCase` | `AuthService`, `ComputeScore` |
| DB tables / columns | `lower_case_with_underscores` | `users`, `user_id`, `looked_at_solution` |
| Go constants (unexported) | `camelCase` | `baseScore`, `decayPerDay` |
| TS/API constants | `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` | `AUTH_INVALID_TOKEN` |
| URLs / routes | `dash-separated-words`, plural | `/api/problems`, `/api/categories/stats` |

## Comments

- Required for all non-trivial logic — especially score/decay math, SQL with non-obvious filters, and middleware context wiring
- The constants in `models/score.go` must always have inline comments explaining the rationale
- No comments that just restate what the code does — explain *why*

## TODOs

```go
// TODO(#42): Add rate limiting to auth endpoints — currently unbounded
```
- Must reference a GitHub issue number
- Include the reason, not just the task

## Code Quality

- ❌ Functions > 50 lines
- ❌ Nesting > 4 levels deep
- ❌ Magic numbers or strings — use named constants
- ❌ Commented-out code left in the codebase
- ❌ `console.log` / `log.Printf` debug statements committed
- ❌ Missing error handling
